            <biogHist>
                <p>John Beaton [Bethune] was born in Badan Mhugaidh near Shieldaig to Finlay Beaton
                    and Isabella Beaton n√©e McBeath. Brought up with six siblings, John is described
                    in the 1861 census under 'Rank, Profession or Occupation' as 'pauper lame'; he
                    appears never to have worked, presumably due to his condition, and lived with
                    his parents for most of his life, until at least 1901 when his father had
                    reached the considerable age of 90. </p>
                <p>John died, unmarried, in 1924 of senile decay and cardiac failure and his nephew
                    Finlay Beaton witnessed the certificate.</p>
                <p>Carmichael collected a charm from John in 1909. </p>
